=http://www.prexus.com/ef/becky/snap.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chardok Quest</span><hr size=1> It's not a problem; grab a few friends and set up camp in a room - have your melee pulls trains to you, the group AEs (smallest AEs) to 'tag' each mob (get onto its hate list, to get the faction hit) whilst the remaining melees wipe them up.<br><br>Once the trains for that area are pulled, your group moves to the next area and the melee pull new trains.<br><br>A nice set of camps is: zonein -> bottom cavern -> barbecue city area (warder area, if you camped the Shroud of Nature) -> through the arches to the two buildings at the base of the mine -> at the top of the slope back to zone-in.<br><br>You can get about 20-30 goblins in each area, and can do the cycle in the time it takes to respawn, which equates to about +300 faction per hour.<br><br>Repeat that for three nights or so, and you have your first ring!  Very easy.  You also get the ability to CR Chardok raids, check on rare spawns, and to buy Louie's Thick and Hearty from Haggle Baron Dry'dn.  :)<br><br>Getting the second ring is quick work, with the exception of the (roughly) three day wait for the Angry Goblin at the end.  The Safehouse marks him as a 5-day spawn, but every single time (on Prexus at least) he's been around the 3-day mark, to within an accuracy of a few hours.<br><br>Once you have ring 2, you can say "I serve the Sarnak" and get a new ring 1!  The pair of rings is pretty much unparalleled for high-end druidry, where you're looking for HP/mana a great deal of the time.  Second only to Crysteria's Crystal Ring, from Vulak'aerr, really.  :)<br><br>Happy faction hunting!<br><br><br>Toodlepip, <p><img src="http://www.prexus.com/ef/becky/kitty.gif" align="right">--<br><b><a href="http://www.suckbird.com/roster/profile.asp?who=Lotusfly">Lotusfly Stewnicely</a></b><br><b><a href="http://www.keepersofthefaith.org">KTF</a></